<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-13728] PushHttpMetricsReporter no longer pushes metrics when network failure is recovered.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-13728</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The class&#160;&lt;b&gt;PushHttpMetricsReporter&lt;/b&gt; no longer pushes metrics when network failure is recovered.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I debugged the code and found the problem here :&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/dc36dedd28ff384218b669de13993646483db966/tools/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/tools/PushHttpMetricsReporter.java#L214-L221&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/dc36dedd28ff384218b669de13993646483db966/tools/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/tools/PushHttpMetricsReporter.java#L214-L221&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When we submit a task to the&#160;&lt;b&gt;ScheduledThreadPoolExecutor&lt;/b&gt; that needs to be executed periodically, if the task throws an exception and is not swallowed, the task will no longer be scheduled to execute.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
